{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% set nav = 'communities' %}
{% block main_class %}{% endblock %}

{% block title %}Sagamok: questions awaiting Council{% endblock %}
{% block description %}A member-led public tracker of questions and records requests still awaiting an answer from Sagamok Chief and Council.{% endblock %}
{% block body_class %}route-sagamok-awaiting-council{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}
<style>
  .awaiting{--maxw:760px;color:var(--ink);font:18px/1.7 var(--sans);-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased}
  .awaiting *{box-sizing:border-box}
  .awaiting .wrap{max-width:var(--maxw);margin:0 auto;padding:40px 22px 64px}
  .awaiting a{color:var(--accent);text-decoration:none}
  .awaiting a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
  .awaiting .crumb{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--ink-3);margin:0 0 16px}
  .awaiting h1{font-size:34px;line-height:1.16;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 12px;color:var(--indigo-deep);font-family:var(--serif)}
  .awaiting .lede{font-size:19px;color:var(--ink-2);margin:0 0 18px}
  .awaiting h2{font-size:24px;line-height:1.25;font-weight:700;margin:44px 0 16px;color:var(--indigo-deep);font-family:var(--serif)}
  .awaiting h3{font-size:20px;line-height:1.25;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 10px;color:var(--indigo-deep);font-family:var(--serif)}
  .awaiting p{margin:0 0 14px}
  .awaiting .item{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-left:4px solid var(--accent);border-radius:0 14px 14px 0;padding:20px 22px;margin:18px 0;box-shadow:0 6px 24px rgba(31,29,26,.06)}
  .awaiting .meta{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink-2);margin:0 0 8px}
  .awaiting .status{display:inline-block;font-size:12px;line-height:1;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em;font-weight:700;color:var(--indigo-deep);background:var(--paper-2);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:999px;padding:7px 9px;margin:0 0 12px}
  .awaiting ul{margin:0 0 18px;padding-left:0;list-style:none}
  .awaiting li{position:relative;padding-left:22px;margin:0 0 10px}
  .awaiting li::before{content:"";position:absolute;left:3px;top:12px;width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--accent)}
  .awaiting .byline{font-size:14px;color:var(--ink-3);margin:34px 0 0;padding-top:16px;border-top:1px solid var(--rule)}
</style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="awaiting">
<div class="wrap">

  <p class="crumb"><a href="/communities">Communities</a> &gt; <a href="/communities/sagamok">Sagamok Anishnawbek</a> &gt; Awaiting Council</p>

  <h1>Sagamok: questions awaiting an answer</h1>
  <p class="lede">A growing record of questions members have put to Sagamok Chief and Council, and to the Nation's offices, that are still awaiting a reply.</p>

  {% set banner_body %}<strong>Member-led and unofficial.</strong> This tracker is independent. It is not the Robinson Huron Treaty Litigation Fund and is not affiliated with it. Each item is framed as a question, tied to a public source, an open meeting, or a written request. <a href="/about#corrections">Tell us what we got wrong</a> and we will correct it.{% endset %}
  {% include 'components/notice.html.twig' with { variant: 'caveat', body: banner_body, label: 'About this page' } only %}

  <h2>Open</h2>

  <article class="item">
    <span class="status">Awaiting</span>
    <h3>1. Member records request</h3>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Asked:</strong> June 10, 2026, to Chief and Council through the Council Secretariat.</p>
    <p>The request asks how the Nation's settlement capital and enterprise investments are governed and what benefit reaches members, including the trust deed, company loans and terms, Finance and Audit Committee independence, committee memberships, and the records-access process. The final signed request, with supplements, was filed July 9, 2026.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="item">
    <span class="status">Awaiting</span>
    <h3>2. Next Chief and Council meeting, and whether members can attend</h3>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Asked:</strong> July 3, 2026, to the Council Secretariat and the Political Office.</p>
    <p>A member asked when the next Chief and Council meeting is, whether it is open to members, and how a member can be heard. The public meeting schedule remains out of date, and meeting agendas are not posted.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="item">
    <span class="status">Awaiting</span>
    <h3>3. The long-term care MOU</h3>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Asked:</strong> June 2026, to Chief and Council through the Council Secretariat.</p>
    <p>The June public announcement said Sagamok signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Whitefish River First Nation, the Town of Espanola, and the Espanola Regional Hospital. Members asked what Council authorized, when, and on what terms. A July 7 staff reply said the signed MOU will be shared "when it becomes available," with no date given, and did not address the request for the authorizing Band Council Resolution.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="item">
    <span class="status">Awaiting</span>
    <h3>4. The members-portal disclosure</h3>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Asked:</strong> June 1, 2026, to the Political Office, delivered to Chief and Council; escalated July 3, 2026.</p>
    <p>A member raised that members-portal pages had been exposed online, asked Council to confirm the issue was fixed, and asked Council to account for it. The exposure has since been resolved. A substantive response to the letter is still outstanding.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="item">
    <span class="status">Awaiting</span>
    <h3>5. The July 20 Elders Forum and day trip</h3>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Asked:</strong> June 2026, to the Political Office.</p>
    <p>Members asked which department owns and funds the event, why an elders program is administered through the Political Office rather than a wellness or service department, and what consideration was given to elder financial wellbeing in scheduling a stop at a casino on a band-organized, band-funded elders trip.</p>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Source:</strong> the Nation's public notice for the Elders Forum, July 20, 2026.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="item">
    <span class="status">Ready to send</span>
    <h3>6. Full draft of the proposed Community Safety By-law</h3>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Prepared:</strong> July 8, 2026, for the Political Office and Council Secretariat.</p>
    <p>The draft request asks for the full current draft of the proposed Community Safety By-law presented by FALLS Law at the July 7, 2026 Chief and Council meeting, plus any plain-language summary or presentation materials shared with Council, the expected member-engagement schedule, and the expected date when Council will be asked to consider or approve the by-law.</p>
    <p>The proposal discussed at the open meeting appeared to deal with removal powers, trespass notices, appeal rights, enforcement officers, penalties, housing implications, and how the law may apply to members and non-members. Members should be able to read the full draft before Council considers it further.</p>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Source:</strong> July 7, 2026 open Chief and Council meeting attended by a member; written request prepared July 8, 2026.</p>
  </article>

  <h2>Answered</h2>
  <p>Nothing here yet. As replies arrive, they will move to this section with the date and a short summary of what was provided.</p>

  <h2>How this list works</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Every item is a question grounded in a public source, an open meeting, or an as-filed document.</li>
    <li>An item stays under Open until the Nation provides a written answer.</li>
    <li>This is a member resource. Corrections are welcome.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="byline">A community resource from the Robinson Huron Treaty hub, member-led and independent. Last updated July 8, 2026.</p>

</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
